
==English==
===Etymology===

Borrowed from {{LL.}} ''interstitium'', from ''[[inter]]'', "between" and [[stitium]], "stoppage."
===Pronunciation===

{{IPA|ˌɪntɚˑstɪʃiəm}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun|interstitia}}

# {{medicine}} An [[interstitial]] space within a tissue or organ.
# {{medicine}} Specifically the tissue between the pulmonary [[alveoli]] and the bloodstream.


